// AssertionTests.AssertingFalseTerminates:
//  ASSERT_DEATH checks whether a specific piece of code results in the program terminating.
//  In this case, the program terminates when it encounters a false condition and 
//  utils::ASSERT checks to see if it displays the error message “Assertion failed: test”.

// AssertionTests.AssertingTrueIsOK:
//  ASSERT_NO_FATAL_FAILURE ensures that when encountered with a true condition, the code 
//  runs without any fatal errors.

// AssertionTests.FatalQuitsImmediately:
// 	Checks to see that upon a fatal error, the program immediately terminates with the error
// 	Message “Fatal error: test”.